f(z) = \sum_{n\ge 0} z^n \sum_{k=0}^{\lfloor n/2 \rfloor} {n-k\choose k}
f(z) = \sum_{k\ge 0} \sum_{\lfloor n/2 \rfloor \ge k} z^n {n-k\choose k} = \sum_{k\ge 0} \sum_{n\ge 2k} {n-k\choose k} z^n = \sum_{k\ge 0} \sum_{n\ge 0} {n+k\choose n} z^{n+2k}.
f(z) = \sum_{k\ge 0} z^{2k} \frac{1}{(1-z)^{k+1}} = \frac{1}{1-z}\frac{1}{1-z^2/(1-z)} = \frac{1}{1-z-z^2}.
